The methodology doc (`AXIOM_IMPLEMENTATION_EVOLUTION.md`) was deferred because no rule extension was warranted. The follow-up findings **reinforce that deferral** — the rule is correct across all four fixtures. There is no observed structured signal in any fixture's unobservable region that would justify extending the rule.

**A worthwhile related doc:** a short note in `Build_Docs/Architecture/` (or as an addendum to `METROLOGY_PRINCIPLES.md`) recording that:
